 1. DVD Descrypter http://www.mrbass.org/dvdrip/

 2. Use 7Zip to remove contents from ios
 3. Use Nero RECODE to convert to mp4 [would love to skip this step but can't figure out how]

Backing up

-&gt; Copy the mpeg4 file
-&gt; COpy the mpeg2 file

Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

Next story: \lang1033\ul [ ] Big Consideration: Write in FIRST PERSON for this one? re: THE THINGS-WATTS (or perhaps my short zombie facebook story) LOVE THIS:\par
Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 November-29-08\par
\b0 - I'd like the bulk of my sci-fi to be positive, like Sawyer`s - positive sci-fi\par
- Think about how the techonlogy would be used, not just as a story device but its side effects, its trival uses\par
- tech that is available to everyone is more likely to change the world\par
\b\f1\fs24 April-10-10\b0\f0\fs20\par
Can a writer manipulte the reader through the use of situational factors and labels.\par
\par
I think this should go into a writing style note and applicable to all stories... think of how to apply this to Rhea story (and the link story) but also a work that is compoletely about deceiving the audience to make the point. (Young Adult)\par
}
</Data1>

Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

Next story: \lang1033\ul [ ] Big Consideration: Write in FIRST PERSON for this one? re: THE THINGS-WATTS (or perhaps my short zombie facebook story) LOVE THIS:\par
Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

Next story: \lang1033\ul [ ] Big Consideration: Write in FIRST PERSON for this one? re: THE THINGS-WATTS (or perhaps my short zombie facebook story) LOVE THIS:\par
Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}"Home," the said\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}"Where?" she said\par

Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

\viewkind4\uc1\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\f0\fs20 Title: Tat Powerful Lie\par

\b\f1\fs24 WRITING PLAN \f2 December-14-10\b0\f0\fs20\par
- aim for under 4000 word stories, primarily sci-fi\par
- Location Locked Content\par
- Day Things Changed -&gt; Out\par
- Satelite Blues --&gt; merge it with telepresence kids?\par
- Telepresence Kids\par
- Fleshsmith OR use it for Deceit and Dreamers\par
- Frog Story (finish)\par
- Take a look at unddecided\par
- Social Worker?\par
\par
Next story: \lang1033\ul [ ] Big Consideration: Write in FIRST PERSON for this one? re: THE THINGS-WATTS (or perhaps my short zombie facebook story) LOVE THIS:\par
Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par
\par
\lang4105\ulnone\par
\par
NEXT: Think something sophistaiced like what Kress would write... researched and quasi historical and INTERESTING... I dunno, I need to clik at something.\par

\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 November-29-08\par
\b0 - I'd like the bulk of my sci-fi to be positive, like Sawyer`s - positive sci-fi\par
- Think about how the techonlogy would be used, not just as a story device but its side effects, its trival uses\par
- tech that is available to everyone is more likely to change the world\par
\b\f1\fs24 April-10-10\b0\f0\fs20\par
Can a writer manipulte the reader through the use of situational factors and labels.\par
\par
I think this should go into a writing style note and applicable to all stories... think of how to apply this to Rhea story (and the link story) but also a work that is compoletely about deceiving the audience to make the point. (Young Adult)\par
}

Next story: \lang1033\ul [ ] Big Consideration: Write in FIRST PERSON for this one? re: THE THINGS-WATTS (or perhaps my short zombie facebook story) LOVE THIS:\par
Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par

 1. DVD Descrypter http://www.mrbass.org/dvdrip/

 2. Use 7Zip to remove contents from ios

-&gt; COpy the mpeg2 file

Here in the storm, I will return to the ice. I've barely even been away, after all; alive for only a few days out of all these endless ages. But I've learned enough in that time. I learned from the wreck that there will be no repairs. I learned from the ice that there will be no rescue. And I learned from the world that there will be no reconciliation. The only hope of escape, now, is into the future; to outlast all this hostile, twisted biomass, to let time and the cosmos change the rules. Perhaps the next time I awaken, this will be a different world.\par
